    • Constructor Detail

      • RootSyntaxAST

        public RootSyntaxAST(SyntaxAnalyzer syntaxAnalyzer)
        This constructor will initialize the RootAST with the AST-Type "ROOT". This will help to debug problems or check the AST for correct syntax. Also it will pass the SyntaxAnalyzer for setting the end of this AST (input file length).
        Parameters:
        syntaxAnalyzer - The SyntaxAnalyzer which get used to parse the tokens.

    • Method Detail

      • parseAST

        public RootSyntaxAST parseAST(AbstractSyntaxAST parentAST,
                              SyntaxAnalyzer syntaxAnalyzer)
        This method will parse the "RootAST" and checks it for correct syntax. The RootAST is used to store all variables, functions etc. Also it is called the "root file" because it is the outers layer of the whole AST. It will just parse annotations and statements and checks if they got parsed right.
        Specified by:
        parseAST in class AbstractSyntaxAST
        Parameters:
        parentAST - The parent of the AST. With it you can check for correct usage of the statement.
        syntaxAnalyzer - The given SyntaxAnalyzer is used for checking the syntax of the current Token list.
        Returns:
        It will return null if an error occurred or a RootAST if it parsed until to the end.
